We live in “a time to refrain from embracing.” When will it be “a time to embrace” again?
When we weep, we yearn to weep together.
The time for embracing will also be beautiful, and the hour is coming soon.
Until then, O Lord, may our season of solitude bear fruit in the lives of those we love, even those we cannot be with.
